[1m5.5.[m [36mHow do I configure Vim to open a file at the last edited location?[m

Vim stores the cursor position of the last edited location for each buffer
in the '"' register. You can use the following autocmd in your .vimrc or
[1m.[m [36mvimrc file to open a file at the last edited location:[m

    au BufReadPost * if line("'\"") > 0 && line("'\"") <= line("$") |
                         \ exe "normal g'\"" | endif

For more information, read

